name: inorganic potassium fertiliser, as K2O to generic market for organo-mineral potassium fertiliser, as K2O | organo-mineral potassium fertiliser, as K2O | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/23923/documentation

This is a renaming activity that connects "inorganic potassium fertiliser, as K2O" with "organo-mineral potassium fertiliser, as K2O". It is assumed that in the shortage of "organo-mineral potassium fertiliser, as K2O", a consumer of it will turn its consumption pattern and use an "inorganic potassium fertiliser, as K2O". In theory, the "inorganic potassium fertiliser, as K2O" can substitute the "organo-mineral potassium fertiliser, as K2O" in an equal mass ratio, considering only the nutrient content.;This dataset is meant to be employed only in the consequential system model where it is assumed that inorganic can replace organic fertiliser. The production volume of this activity is set to zero so it does not react with attributional supply chains.

The activity starts with the reception of inorganic potassium fertiliser, as K2O.

The activity ends with organo-mineral potassium fertiliser, as K2O being ready for transportation.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/016:Support activities to agriculture and post-harvest crop activities/0161:Support activities for crop production

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Inventory is based on the nutrient content of the fertiliser.
